  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with a matching lid with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and&nbsp;1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>chicken stock cube</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled&nbsp;water</strong> and&nbsp;a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;to a large bowl and mix well</p>\r\n<p>Grate 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>red cabbage</strong>, discarding the tough&nbsp;stem</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>grated cabbage</strong>&nbsp;to the bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside until later to pickle slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1348.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>tahini</strong>, <strong>oregano</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, 50ml&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water,</strong>&nbsp;a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and the <strong>honey </strong>in a bowl &ndash; this is your<strong> tahini sauce</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the<strong> chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>and slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
